      "text": "Communication is the process by which meaning is assigned to or exchanged between individuals through a common system of symbols, signs and behaviors. It involves transmission of a message between an initiator and a receiver and since the essence of a message is for the parties to understand each other, they play the roles of initiator and receiver simultaneously. "
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "f5a4511a0ea08a9e",
      "text": "Communication or lack of it, is a major factor in conflict generation and management. Indeed, communication and perception are complementary. Where there is scanty or no communication among individuals or groups, there is likely to be a wrong perception."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "753d2400215daa4e",
      "text": "In a conflict involving farmers and herdsmen especially the Bororos, there is a major handicap as the two groups are likely to have difficulty in communicating with each other since they speak different languages and, as such, they may not understand each other. The farmers do not speak Fulfude while the herdsmen (Bororos especially) do not speak Yoruba. When a conflict occurs between them, there is tendency for it to escalate. This is the scenario that manifests in the process of transaction between pastoralists and farmers in Saki West Local Government area.  "
